<sn><md>#### Important Fraction–Percentage Conversions

| Fraction                                      | Fraction                                      |
| :-------------------------------------------- | :-------------------------------------------- |
| $1 = 100%$                                    | $\frac{1}{6} = 16\frac{2}{3}% \approx 16.67%$ |
| $\frac{1}{2} = 50%$                           | $\frac{1}{7} = 14\frac{2}{7}% \approx 14.28%$ |
| $\frac{1}{3} = 33\frac{1}{3}% \approx 33.33%$ | $\frac{1}{8} = 12.5%$                         |
| $\frac{2}{3} = 66\frac{2}{3}% \approx 66.67%$ | $\frac{1}{9} = 11.11%$                        |
| $\frac{1}{4} = 25%$                           | $\frac{1}{10} = 10%$                          |
| $\frac{3}{4} = 75%$                           | |
| $\frac{1}{5} = 20%$                           |   |
</md></sn><sn><md>Qna {.text-end}

**1. What percent of 12 is 18? [36th BCS]**<br>
a. 110<br> b. 125<br> c.`150`<br> d. 160

+++ check
Let $x%$ of 12 = 18
$$
12 \times \frac{x}{100} = 18
$$
$$
x = \frac{18 \times 100}{12} = 150
$$

**Answer: 150%**
+++

---

**2. $\frac{1}{2}$ is what percent of $\frac{3}{4}$? [26th BCS]**<br>
a. 120%<br> b. 125%<br> c. 140%<br> d. `150%`

+++ check
Let $\frac{1}{2}$ be $x%$ of $\frac{3}{4}$
$$
\frac{1}{2} \times \frac{x}{100} = \frac{3}{4}
$$
$$
x = \frac{3 \times 100 \times 2}{4} = 150
$$

**Answer: 150%**
+++

---

