**41. If 120% of a number ‘A’ is equal to 80% of another number ‘B’, then what is (A + B)? [NSI Assistant Director - 2019]**<br>
a. 1.5A<br> b. 2A<br> c. `2.5A`<br> d. 3A

+++ check
Given:
$$
120% \text{ of } A = 80% \text{ of } B
$$
$$
A \times \frac{120}{100} = B \times \frac{80}{100}
$$
$$
\frac{B}{A} = \frac{120}{80} = 1.5 \Rightarrow B = 1.5A
$$
$$
A + B = A + 1.5A = 2.5A
$$

**Answer: 2.5A**
+++

